<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Employment" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Employment,</orth> 1) use: <cit><quote>wit may be made a Jack-a-Lent, when 'tis upon ill e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.135" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 135</bibl></cit>. <emph>the which</emph> (money) <cit><quote>he hath detained for lewd --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.90" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 90</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. V, 3, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.77" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 77</bibl>.<lb />2) office, service, commission: <emph>fit for</emph> <cit><quote>great e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. V, 4, 157</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>you have no e. for me,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.280" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 280</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 2.35" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.2.140" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 140</bibl> <cit><quote>(your ladyship's in all desired e.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 2.2.71" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 2, 71</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.204" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 204</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 2.1.48" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 II, 1, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.262" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 262</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.5.110" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 110</bibl>. <emph>at your e.</emph> == at your service, <bibl n="shak. jn 1.198" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 198</bibl>. <cit><quote>upon hasty e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.139" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 139</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 136</bibl>.
<lb />3) work, business: <cit><quote>what e. have we here?</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.91" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 5, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>is there not wars? is there not e.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.2.85" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 2, 85</bibl></cit>.
